        "en": "1. Ensure subject does not consume anything (no food, beverages/water, tobacco, chewing gum) for 10 minutes prior to taking the sample.\n\n\n\n2. Instruct Subject:\"Please carefully put this tube in your mouth and move it from one side of your mouth to the other to get saliva from your entire mouth (your cheek, under your tongue, and on top of your tongue).  Be sure not to chew or suck on the tube.  I will tell you when to stop.\"NOTE:IFthe participant asks what the sample is for, say: \"This is to look for small amounts of chemicals, medications, or drugs that could be in your body\"3. Adequate sample has been collected when the sample collector begins to turn blue. In the absence of a blue color, the sample may be tested after collecting for 4 minutes.\n\n\n\n4. If test results are unexpected based on self-report and/or clinical observation: Repeat the test right away using new cassette. Instruct Subject:\"We need to do that one more time, please do the same thing using this new test.  Carefully put this tube in your mouth and move it from one side of your mouth to the other to get saliva from your entire mouth.\""
